<html>
<head>
  <script>
  $(function() {
     $( "#datepicker" ).datepicker({
      showOn: "button",
      buttonImage: "/images/calendar.jpg",
      buttonImageOnly: true
    });
  });
  </script>
</head>
<body>
<%= form_for(@plan) do |f| %>
  <% if @plan.errors.any? %>
    <div id="error_explanation">
      <h2><%= pluralize(@plan.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this plan from being saved:</h2>

      <ul>
      <% @plan.errors.full_messages.each do |msg| %>
        <li><%= msg %></li>
      <% end %>
      </ul>
    </div>
  <% end %>
  <div class="span11 offset well">
  <div class="form-horizontal">
    <div class="accordion " id="accordion2">
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <div class="accordion-heading">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapseOne">
           <button class="btn btn-info"> New Plan</button>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-body collapse in">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :plan_title %><br />
      Give the plan a title, name or code so it's easily identified on the plan list menu<br />
    <%= f.text_field :plan_title %>
  </div>
  
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :plan_sponsor %><br />
    Who is responsible for keeping this plan realitistic, communicateed and applicable? (quite a job, right?)<br />
    <%= f.text_field :sponsor %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :launch_responsible %><br />
    There should be someone who is authorized to lunch this plan (sometimes the Plan Sponsor)<br />
    <%= f.text_field :responsible %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :recoverable_response %><br />
    <%= f.text_field :recoverableresponse %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :plan_status %><br />
    Describe the status of the plan. Only productive plans are considered "live" plans!<br />
    <%= f.select :planstatus, [[' ',' '],['Proposed','Proposed'],['Design','Design'],
    ['Transition','Transition'],['Production','Production'],['Retired','Retired']] %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :recoverable_plan_type %><br />
    <%= f.text_field :recoverableplantype %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :losstype %><br />
    <%= f.text_field :losstype %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :emergency_response %><br />
    <%= f.text_field :emergencyresponse %>
  </div>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.label :review_date%><br />
    <%= f.text_field :review, :id=> :datepicker %>
  </div>
 
 </div>
  </div>
 </div>  

 <div class="accordion-group">
        <div class="accordion-heading">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapsefour">
            <button class="btn btn-info"> Objective & Criteria &nbsp;<i class="icon-chevron-down"></i></button>
            
          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapsefour" class="accordion-body collapse">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
            <div class="field">
             <%= f.label :plan_objective %><br>
             Describe the plan objective, it should be something short and straightforward to understand.<br />
            <%= f.text_area :plan_objective %>
         </div>
         <div class="field">
            <%= f.label :audit_metric %><br />
            Continuity plans without regular testing and audits are doomed to fail. Set your audit metric criteria (Response time?, etc)<br />
            <%= f.text_area :auditmetric %>
        </div>
        <div class="field">
          <%= f.label :sucess_criteria %><br />
          Define a success criteria for the metric you have just defined (Under 2 hs, etc)<br />
          <%= f.text_area :sucesscriteria %>
       </div>
        <div class="field">
          <%= f.label :launch_criteria %><br />
         Describe the criteria the plan responsible should use to know if it's appropiate to kick the plan or not in the case of an emergency.<br />
         <%= f.text_area :launchcriteria %>
         </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>    
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <div class="accordion-heading">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapsethree">
            <button class="btn btn-info"> Document Control</button>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapsethree" class="accordion-body collapse">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
            <div class="control-group">
              <b> Document Title </b><br/>
              
            </div>
            <div class="control-group">
              <b> Attachment </b><br/>
              <%= f.file_field :attachment %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
 
     <!--  <div class="accordion-group">
        <div class="accordion-heading">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapsefour">
            Governance Risk and Compliance
          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapsefour" class="accordion-body collapse">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
            <p>Governance Risk and Compliance</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div> -->
      <div class="accordion-group">
        <div class="accordion-heading">
          <a class="accordion-toggle" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion2" href="#collapsefive">
            <button class="btn btn-info"> Approval , Review and  Distribution</button>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div id="collapsefive" class="accordion-body collapse">
          <div class="accordion-inner">
            <p>Approval , Review and  Distribution</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <br>
   <div class="actions">
    <%= f.submit '+ Add New BCM Plan', :class =>  "pure-button pure-button-primary"%>
    <%= link_to 'Cancel', plans_path , :class => "pure-button pure-button-primary"%>
  </div>
<% end %>
</div>
</body>
</html>

